26/05/2004
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- Macedonia might open accession negotiations with the EU in 2006 or 2007, according to Gerald Knaus, director of the European Stability Initiative. Speaking on Tuesday (25 May) at the 10th Thessaloniki Southeast European forum, Kraus said that Macedonia could serve as a "key" for Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, and Serbia-Montenegro.
Also Tuesday, the 2nd national forum on accelerated integration into the EU started in Skopje. The event aims to co-ordinate efforts of national institutions to speed up the reform process and implementation of the Stabilisation and Association Agreement. (Utrinski Vesnik - 26/05/04; A1 TV, Makfax, NATO press release - 25/05/04)
